cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL 

The paper deals with computer vision and robotics, specifically with 3D LiDAR scans and Convolutional Neural Networks. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) and cs.RO (Robotics) are the most likely sub-categories. The use of a triplet loss function and hard-negative mining strategy suggests a focus on machine learning, which could place the paper in cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper's emphasis on descriptor extraction and place recognition could also place it in cs.CL (Computation and Language).
